  "text": "The problem of how to select from D the smallest number of k atoms d n , n = 1 . . . , k, such that f k − f < ρ, for a given tolerance parameter ρ, is an NP-hard problem [CITATION_1] . In practical applications one looks for 'tractable sparse' solutions. This is to say a representation involving a number of k-terms, with k acceptable small in relation to N . The simple MP approach to tackle this problem evolves by successive approximations as follows [CITATION_2] : Setting k = 0 and starting with an initial approximation f 0 = 0 and residual r 0 = f the algorithm iterates by sub-decomposing the k-th order residue into",
